abstract: New York billionaire and presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg led a high-powered charge against President Donald Trump's climate policies Tuesday, assuring activists, scientists and politicians from around the world that Americans are committed to reducing greenhouse gas emissions “even with a climate change denier in the White House."
snippet: New York billionaire and presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg led a high-powered charge against President Donald Trump's climate policies Tuesday, assuring activists, scientists and politicians from around the world that Americans are committe...
lead_paragraph: MADRID — New York billionaire and presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg led a high-powered charge against President Donald Trump's climate policies Tuesday, assuring activists, scientists and politicians from around the world that Americans are committed to reducing greenhouse gas emissions “even with a climate change denier in the White House."
headline_main: Bloomberg Tells UN Climate Talks: You Can Count on the US
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Tells UN Climate Talks: You Can Count on the US

abstract: Devastating bushfires that blanketed Australia's largest city with hazardous smoke this week have heightened public anger and raised political pressure on the government to do more to tackle climate change.
snippet: Devastating bushfires that blanketed Australia's largest city with hazardous smoke this week have heightened public anger and raised political pressure on the government to do more to tackle climate change.
lead_paragraph: SYDNEY — Devastating bushfires that blanketed Australia's largest city with hazardous smoke this week have heightened public anger and raised political pressure on the government to do more to tackle climate change.
headline_main: Hazardous Sydney Smoke Turns Up Heat in Australia's Climate Politics
headline_print_headline: Hazardous Sydney Smoke Turns Up Heat in Australia's Climate Politics

abstract: Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad has vowed to bring back billions of dollars allegedly stolen from state fund 1Malaysia Development Bhd (1MDB), co-founded by his predecessor Najib Razak.
snippet: Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad has vowed to bring back billions of dollars allegedly stolen from state fund 1Malaysia Development Bhd (1MDB), co-founded by his predecessor Najib Razak.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad has vowed to bring back billions of dollars allegedly stolen from state fund 1Malaysia Development Bhd (1MDB), co-founded by his predecessor Najib Razak.
headline_main: Explainer: Malaysia's Mega 1MDB Scandal That Has Scalded Goldman Sachs
headline_print_headline: Explainer: Malaysia's Mega 1MDB Scandal That Has Scalded Goldman Sachs

abstract: Foreign meddling was once the most feared source of online deception before critical elections. Now, some candidates themselves are turning to such manipulative tactics.
snippet: Foreign meddling was once the most feared source of online deception before critical elections. Now, some candidates themselves are turning to such manipulative tactics.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Manipulated Twitter accounts, doctored videos, dodgy websites and questions of foreign meddling. In just six weeks, the campaign leading up to Britain’s general election this Thursday, one of its most important votes in a generation, has had a taste of what the dark arts of online campaigning have to offer.

abstract: Could the latest round of strikes spell the beginning of the end for Emmanuel Macron?
snippet: Could the latest round of strikes spell the beginning of the end for Emmanuel Macron?
lead_paragraph: France is paralyzed. Since a general strike began on Thursday, planes have been grounded, mail delivery stopped and schools closed, and trains remain in their depots. Even lawyers are staying home. Some 800,000 people took to the street across the country last Thursday, and another major demonstration is planned for today as the strike continues. As one participant put it to the French newspaper Mediapart, the mass mobilizations are meant as a rebuke to “Macron and his world.”
